movie_name: After Truth: Disinformation and the Cost of Fake News
short_description: A look at the ongoing threat caused by the phenomenon of "fake news" in the U.S., focusing on the real-life consequences that disinformation, conspiracy theories and false news stories have on the average citizen.

facts_and_links: {'Trivia': ['Jacob Wohl and Jack Burkman, two of the people featured in this documentary as perpetrating and spreading disinformation, were charged on October 1, 2020 by the Michigan Attorney General Dana Nessel for allegedly operating a voter suppression campaign of robocalls to largely Democratic voters in Detroit highlighting the false claim that the information provided in registering for vote-by-mail would be used for nefarious purposes beyond the requested voting materials.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11615038/trivia/?ref_=tt_dyk_trv'], 'Quotes': ['Self - Berkman Klein Center, Harvard University: Mainstream media needs to understand that it is operating in a propaganda-rich environment. There are no two realities. There is an intentional deception on one side, and there is an honest if imperfect process of trying to get as near to the truth as we can on the other.', 'https://www.imdb.com/title/tt11615038/quotes/?ref_=tt_dyk_qu']}
